This paper deals with the application of nonmonotonic constructs in knowledge representation, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also extensively investigates the computational complexity of Circumscription, which is a logical inference technique, making it relevant to the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with knowledge bases and their formulation, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing and semantic policy formulation, which are topics in computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with computational complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
